<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="958" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1059,573,683]" pageId="5" pageNumber="958">
R e m a r k s: First record for Sicily! South-European, known only from a few Countries. In 
<collectingCountry box="[245,292,603,625]" name="Italy" pageId="5" pageNumber="958">Italy</collectingCountry>
it is recorded only from the extremely north regions (
<collectingRegion box="[887,988,603,625]" country="Italy" name="Piemonte" pageId="5" pageNumber="958">Piedmont</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion country="Italy" name="Valle d'Aosta" pageId="5" pageNumber="958">Valle d’Aosta</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[244,352,632,654]" country="Italy" name="Lombardia" pageId="5" pageNumber="958">Lombardy</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[363,574,632,654]" country="Italy" name="Trentino-Alto Adige" pageId="5" pageNumber="958">Trentino-Alto Adige</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[628,849,632,654]" country="Italy" name="Friuli-Venezia Giulia" pageId="5" pageNumber="958">Friuli-Venezia Giulia</collectingRegion>
), so the extension of the range to the south is remarkable.
</paragraph>
